B.3 Computation of Contraction Rate

```python
def compute_contraction_rate(trajectory):
    """
    trajectory: list of state vectors (e.g., concatenated mu, sigma, delta) over time.
    Returns the estimated contraction rate (log of ratio of successive differences).
    """
    diffs = [np.linalg.norm(trajectory[i+1] - trajectory[i]) for i in range(len(trajectory)-1)]
    rates = [np.log(diffs[i+1]/diffs[i]) for i in range(len(diffs)-1)]
    return np.mean(rates)  # should be negative for exponential decay
```

